### Step 6: Format for Jira (Dual-Field Format)

**CRITICAL**: Stories must use **dual-field** Jira format:

- **Description**: In the **Jira UI / REST API** (HRREC on Jira Server), the Description field is **Atlassian wiki markup**, not GitHub Flavored Markdown. Use **`h2.`** / **`h3.`**, and **wiki bold** for persona/Gherkin tokens as **single** asterisks in REST payloads — `*As a*`, `*I want*`, `*So that*`, `*Given*`, `*When*`, `*Then*`, `*And*` (matches `GET /rest/api/2/issue/{key}?fields=description` on HRREC). **Do not** use markdown-style `**As a**` inside wiki bodies for `PUT` / `setJiraTicketField` — Jira can show mangled triple asterisks. Translate Git `**Given**` to `*Given*` when building the wiki string. Use **`[label|url]`** links and wiki tables when calling **`setJiraTicketField`** or **`PUT /issue/{key}`**. Sending GFM (`##`, `[text](url)`) causes broken nested numbering and non-clickable links. Encode underscores in URLs as **`%5F`** so wiki does not parse `_…_` as italic. **DoR table:** header row `||Criterion||Any blocking issues…||` only; **every data row** starts with a **single** `|` and keeps **two** columns using **`|text| |`** for an empty Notes cell (space between pipes). **Do not** start a data row with `||` and **do not** end rows with only `||` — that drops the second column in the editor. The fenced **markdown** block below is for **drafts / reviews in Git**; canonical **wiki** for MCP pushes may live in a paired **`.jirawiki`** file **when the initiative documents one** (see **Initiative story supplements** above).
- **Acceptance Criteria** (custom field / SECOND PART): Jira wiki **table shell only** — **header row + empty data rows** (no prefilled AC IDs or scenario titles). Populate rows during refinement when the team locks AC. Do **not** paste this table into the Description.

**Jira Description Field (FIRST PART) — GFM draft for Git / PM review (do not paste raw into REST)**:
```markdown
## User story

**As a** [persona]  
**I want** [goal]  
**So that** [benefit]  

## Scenarios

### Scenario 1: [Scenario title]

**Given** [precondition]  
**When** [action]  
**Then** [outcome]

### Scenario 2: [Scenario title]

**Given** [precondition]  
**When** [action]  
**Then** [outcome]

(2–4 scenarios; use **tight** two-space line breaks between **Given** / **When** / **Then** when there are no intervening **And** lines — see Step 5.)

## Definition of Ready

| **Criterion** | **Any blocking issues to being ready / Notes** |
| We understand the value this work provides to customers and how it supports the product vision. | |
| We have clearly defined, understand, and agree on the Acceptance Criteria. | |
| We have no blocking open questions. | |
| There are no dependencies blocking completion. | |
| We agree on the Manual and Automation testing approach. | |
| We agree on the customer documentation impacts. | |
| We have relatively sized the Story. | |
| We can complete the Story according to our Workday Definition of Done in a sprint. | |
| We have documented our discussions and the key decision points. | |
| We have discussed toggles | |

## Notes

- *(Optional.)* If the initiative **story supplement** defines default Notes bullets (design, PRD, runbooks), paste them here. Otherwise omit this section or add PM-supplied links only.
```

**DoR table rules (GFM drafts in Git)**:
- Header row only, then data rows — **no** GFM separator row such as `| :--- | :--- |` (Jira often renders it as an empty junk row).
- Bold both header cells: `**Criterion**`, `**Any blocking issues to being ready / Notes**`.
- Leave the second column empty (`| |`) on each criterion row for team notes during refinement.

**`## Notes` (GFM draft) / `h2. Notes` (Jira wiki)**: Same placement: **after** the Definition of Ready table. **Do not** invent initiative-specific URLs in **430**—copy the exact bullets and link text from the initiative’s **`STORY_WRITING_SUPPLEMENT.md`** (or whatever path CONTEXT / epic draft / **400** handoff names). In **wiki**, use `* ` list lines and `[label|url]` with `%5F` for underscores inside URLs. Omit the Notes section entirely only when the PM explicitly wants no external references and the supplement does not require defaults.

