## Quality Standards

### Always
- ✅ **Create or resolve Jira epic in Step 1b** before creating stories (standard chain: create from epic draft after 420 HITL)
- ✅ Run **Step 1c** (epic scenario ledger) before drafting when multiple stories are created in one run or when the epic already has child issues
- ✅ Consult Deployment Agent MCP for Workday context
- ✅ Search functional knowledge for workflows
- ✅ Use XO MCP for existing-task/service features to ground AC and BDD in real constraints
- ✅ Apply SPIDR splitting if stories are too large
- ✅ Write stories following INVEST principles
- ✅ Generate 2-4 distinct BDD scenarios per story (mandatory)
- ✅ Every Gherkin clause on its **own line**; **tight** Given/When/Then uses two trailing spaces + newline (see Step 5); **Given** / **When** / **Then** lines have **no** terminal `.`
- ✅ **Definition of Ready** table in Description (bold headers, **no** `| :--- |` separator row)
- ✅ Use dual-field Jira format (Description + **Acceptance Criteria** field with **blank** wiki grid at create unless PM requests populated rows)
- ✅ Link stories to the resolved epic key; add **value slice** label and **`M{n}`** when milestones apply
- ✅ **Step 6a**: Apply **`319-copy-review.mdc`** to user-visible copy in stories before Jira create/update (invoke **060** via **319** for legal-sensitive strings)

### Never
- ❌ Write stories without consulting Deployment Agent
- ❌ Skip functional knowledge search
- ❌ Create Jira epics or stories when part of backlog chain without confirmation of 420 HITL approval
- ❌ Use a pre-existing story map file as sufficient proof of approval when invoked by 400
- ❌ Write fewer than 2 or more than 4 scenarios per story
- ❌ Put Gherkin clauses on same line (violates formatting rule)
- ❌ Use single-field Jira format (must use dual-field)
- ❌ Forget **value slice** labels; forget **`M{n}`** when the initiative defines milestones
- ❌ Write technical tasks instead of user stories
- ❌ Skip SPIDR splitting for large stories
- ❌ Ship new or changed **UI copy** in Jira without a **319**-level editorial pass (labels, validation, errors, notifications in Description/AC/BDD)

